{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Poison|type2=Dark}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Drapion}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Poison|prevnum=451|prev=Skorupi|nextnum=453|next=Croagunk|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Drapion\n|jname=ドラピオン\n|tmname=Dorapion\n|ndex=452\n|sdex=128\n|u2dex=202\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=016\n|abrow=174\n|obrow=263\n|opbrow=051\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Poison\n|type2=Dark\n|category=Ogre Scorpion\n|height-ftin=4\'03"\n|height-m=1.3\n|weight-lbs=135.6\n|weight-kg=61.5\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Battle Armor\n|ability2=Sniper\n|abilityd=Keen Eye\n|egggroupn=2\n|egggroup1=Bug\n|egggroup2=Water 3\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evde=2\n|expyield=175\n|oldexp=204\n|lv100exp=1,250,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Purple\n|catchrate=45\n|body=14\n|pokefordex=drapion\n|generation=4\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Drapion\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ドラピオン\'\'\' \'\'Dorapion\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Poison|Dark}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s from {{p|Skorupi}} starting at [[level]] 40.\n\n==Biology==\nDrapion is a large, purple, scorpion-like Pokémon. Its eyes are a pointed shape, with blue-colored upper portions. Drapion has two small, pointed protrusions between its eyes, and one on the back on its head. Drapion also has protrusions on its jaws, two on the upper and three on the lower, with large, fang-like, white-colored features extending from its mouth. Its body is composed of many violet-to-lavender body segments which ends with a tail with two stingers. Drapion has four segmented legs with pointed toes. Its most distinguished feature is its huge claws. It can turn its head 180 degrees.\n\nDrapion is a very aggressive Pokémon, attacking anything that enters its territory. It has a sturdy build and takes pride in its strength, being able to take down foes even without the use of its deadly toxin. It has enough power to easily scrap a car.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Paul Drapion.png|thumb|left|250px|Drapion in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nDrapion debuted in \'\'[[DP020|Mutiny in the Bounty!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[J|Pokémon Hunter J]]. It was used to battle [[Ash\'s Pikachu]], {{AP|Aipom}}, and {{AP|Turtwig}}. It reappeared in \'\'[[DP072|Pokémon Ranger and the Kidnapped Riolu! (Part 2)]]\'\', where J ordered it to wrap its claws around {{Ash}}\'s midsection and squeeze tightly on it.\n\nA Drapion appeared in \'\'[[DP099|A Trainer and Child Reunion!]]\'\', under the ownership of {{EF|Aaron}}. It briefly reappeared in \'\'[[DP100|Aiding the Enemy!]]\'\', where it battled [[Cynthia\'s Garchomp]] but lost.\n\nA Drapion debuted in \'\'[[DP186|Familiarity Breeds Strategy!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Paul]]. It was used to battle Ash in that episode, as well as \'\'[[DP187|A Real Rival Rouser!]]\'\' and \'\'[[DP188|Battling a Thaw in Relations!]]\'\'. It managed to defeat {{AP|Buizel}}, {{AP|Staraptor}}, and {{AP|Torterra}} before losing to {{AP|Gliscor}}. It is unknown whether it is the same one he tried to {{pkmn2|caught|catch}} in \'\'[[DP081|Chim - Charred!]]\'\'.\n\nA Drapion appeared in \'\'[[XY094|From A to Z!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Celosia]]. It made further appearances in \'\'[[XY102|Meeting at Terminus Cave!]]\'\', \'\'[[XY132|A Towering Takeover!]]\'\', and \'\'[[XY134|The Right Hero for the Right Job!]]\'\'.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Drapion appeared in \'\'[[DP081|Chim - Charred!]]\'\'.\n\nA Drapion appeared in \'\'[[DP091|One Team, Two Team, Red Team, Blue Team!]]\'\', under the ownership of the [[Pokémon Summer Academy]]. It was used by one of the students in the first leg of the [[Pokémon Triathlon]].\n\nA Drapion appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[DP128|A Pyramiding Rage!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Reggie]]. It was used to battle {{FB|Pyramid King|Brandon}}.\n\nA Drapion appeared in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M10|Giratina and the Sky Warrior]]\'\'.\n\nA Drapion appeared in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M13|Zoroark: Master of Illusions]]\'\'.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP020|Drapion|Ash\'s Pokédex|Drapion, the Ogre Scorp Pokémon. Its claws give off a deadly poison and they are powerful enough to turn an automobile into scrap iron.}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP186|Drapion|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Drapion, the Ogre Scorp Pokémon, and the evolved form of {{p|Skorupi}}. With its sturdy body, Drapion takes pride in its strength, defeating opponents without the need for poison.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Scientist Kricketune Drapion Adventures.png|thumb|Drapion in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Darkrai Mission Story: Pokémon Ranger Vatonage - the Comic manga===\nA Drapion appeared in \'\'[[PRV4|Mission Complete]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon [[Kincaid]] controlled.\n\n===In the Pocket Monsters Diamond & Pearl manga===\nA Drapion appeared in [[PDP03]].\n\n===In the Pocket Monsters Platinum: Aim to Be Battle King!! manga===\nDrapion appeared under the ownership of a Trainer who battled [[Yū Shirogane|Yū]]\'s {{p|Lucario}}.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nIn \'\'[[PS362|Dramatic Drapion & Crafty Kricketune I]]\'\', two {{tc|Scientist}}s working for [[Team Galactic]] fought {{adv|Diamond}}, {{adv|Pearl}}, and {{adv|Platinum}} while guarding [[Lake Valor]]. One of these scientists used a Drapion, whose ability to turn its head 180 degrees angle it to find Diamond\'s hiding {{p|Munchlax}}, {{adv|Lax}}, with ease. Drapion reappeared in a flashback in \'\'[[PS391|Luring in a Lickilicky]]\'\'.\n\nA Drapion appeared in \'\'[[PS418|Deprogramming Porygon-Z]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{tc|School Kid}}.\n\n{{EF|Aaron}}\'s Drapion debuted in \'\'[[PS423|Tackling Togekiss]]\'\'.\n\nA Drapion appeared in \'\'[[PAXY30|Pinsir Changes]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Diamond and Pearl Adventure! manga===\n[[B-2]] of [[Team Galactic]] uses a Drapion while attacking [[Hareta]] on [[Iron Island]] in \'\'[[DPA10|Serious Training on Iron Island!!]]\'\'. The ensuing battle causes Hareta\'s {{p|Shinx}} to evolve into {{p|Luxio}}.\n\nAnother Drapion was conditioned by [[Charon]] into a mindless battle machine in \'\'[[DPA32|Charon Must Be Stopped!]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Drapion (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n* {{g|Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Time and Explorers of Darkness}}: Drapion is part of [[Team AWD]], a team that pursues the challenges of Zero Isle.\n* {{g|Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Sky}}: [[Team AWD]] are shown in the [[Team Charm]] Special Episode, being the major antagonists of the story.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Poison|type2=Dark}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|num1=128|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Diamond|entry=It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Pearl|entry=Its body is encased in a sturdy shell. Its head rotates 180 degrees, eliminating blind spots.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Platinum|entry=Possessing a sturdy build, it takes pride in its strength, taking down foes without using toxins.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=HeartGold|v2=SoulSilver|entry=It attacks people and Pokémon that cross the desert. This has only furthered its bad reputation.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=202|label1={{gameabbrev5|B2W2}}:}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black|v2=White|t=FFF|entry=Possessing a sturdy build, it takes pride in its strength, taking down foes without using toxins.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=It takes pride in its strength. Even though it can tear foes apart, it finishes them off with powerful poison.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=016|label1=Mountain|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=It takes great pride in its strength. Even though it can tear foes apart, it finishes them off wi